  "notes": [
    "This case report describes a rare presentation of pseudo-Cushing's syndrome induced by pheochromocytoma, which has not been previously reported in the literature.",
    "The negative ACTH and CRH immunostaining ruled out ectopic ACTH secretion, confirming the diagnosis of pseudo-Cushing's syndrome rather than true Cushing's syndrome.",
    "The proposed mechanism involves catecholamine-induced hypermetabolic state leading to HPA axis overactivation with a positive feedback loop involving cortisol."
  ]
